http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Drunk-man-drowns-in-pit/article13977446.ece

A 55-year-old man drowned after slipping into a water-filled stone quarry pit at Bettahalasur, in Chikkajala police station limits, on Saturday. The deceased, Iraiah, was a construction labourer and resident of Vidyanagar Cross.According to the police, they were alerted by locals who saw his body. A team from the Fire and Emergency Services recovered the body.The police claimed that Iraiah had picked a quarrel with his family. He was a chronic alcoholic. They suspect that he was inebriated when he slipped into the quarry pit. They are waiting for the post-mortem report to ascertain cause of death.